The paper proposes a method for learning knowledge graph embeddings for entity alignment, which involves generating long paths across KGs and modeling them with a novel recurrent skipping network. This involves techniques from artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), such as recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and residual learning. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on a series of datasets constructed from real-world KGs, which involves techniques from databases (DB) and information retrieval (IR). Additionally, the paper compares the proposed method to state-of-the-art embedding-based EA methods, which involves techniques from natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.IR, in that order.
